It's because they were created in Jehovah God's image.

00:18:39.319 --> 00:18:43.000
Each one is in a dedicated relationship with him.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:49.000
They are praying to Jehovah Jehovah is listening to their prayers and answering their prayers.

00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:52.240
And also the sheep belong to Jehovah, don't they?

00:18:52.240 --> 00:18:56.839
Purchase with the precious blood of his only begotten son.

00:18:56.839 --> 00:19:01.599
And in Bethel we have an added reason to give them honor because each one has received

00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:04.519
his or her assignment from Jehovah.

00:19:04.519 --> 00:19:09.119
The friends in our department, this is their sacred service, this is their assignment

00:19:09.119 --> 00:19:12.119
given to them from Jehovah and they know it well.

00:19:12.119 --> 00:19:17.400
And so each one deserves respect and honor.

00:19:17.400 --> 00:19:23.400
Well how will they sense that we truly honor them from the heart?

00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:31.559
They will sense it when we take note of their work and commend them frequently and sincerely.

00:19:31.559 --> 00:19:36.559
They'll sense it when we follow through on their requests promptly.

00:19:36.559 --> 00:19:40.880
And they'll sense it when we listen to their suggestions to improve the work.

00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:45.079
And when they do that, if they should suggest an improvement, it doesn't mean that they

00:19:45.079 --> 00:19:49.200
are challenging our authority, it doesn't mean that they're being presumptuous, it doesn't

00:19:49.200 --> 00:19:52.000
mean that we were doing it wrong before.

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:57.039
Even Jehovah invited suggestions from his angels in the case of Ahab, didn't he?

00:19:57.039 --> 00:20:00.480
And he approved one of their suggestions.

00:20:00.480 --> 00:20:06.000
Well in these and other ways we can show honor to our workmates.

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:10.900
