00:20:20.180 --> 00:20:26.259
To what characterized Jesus ministry, may it characterize your service as well.

00:20:26.259 --> 00:20:31.579
And as we learn sisters can do that through your example and your words, brothers can do

00:20:31.579 --> 00:20:38.299
that in addition to that by approaching your assignment as a shepherd and also by truly

00:20:38.299 --> 00:20:43.500
taking the lead in showing honor and respect to others.

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:48.220
There's no doubt that Jesus was eager to show Jehovah that He benefited from the fine

00:20:48.299 --> 00:20:51.180
training that He received from Him.

00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:57.299
And so not only did He do what Jehovah asked Him to do, He carried it out in the way that

00:20:57.299 --> 00:20:59.539
Jehovah wanted Him to carry it out.

00:20:59.539 --> 00:21:07.059
Well we know that you too are eager to apply the good things that you learn in Gilead.

00:21:07.059 --> 00:21:11.099
And so as you begin to think about maybe some of the things that you will do differently

00:21:11.099 --> 00:21:17.140
when you arrive at your assignment, give close attention to how you will carry out your

00:21:17.140 --> 00:21:21.779
work, show that you have come to minister.

00:21:21.779 --> 00:21:27.299
And when you do that, you will show that you truly benefited from your Gilead training.

00:21:27.299 --> 00:21:32.500
The brothers will love you and above all you will have the favor and approval of our

00:21:32.500 --> 00:21:33.740
God, Jehovah.
